{
  "slug": "math-olympiad",
  "name": "Math Olympiad",
  "type": "plugin",
  "description": "Solve competition math (IMO, Putnam, USAMO) with adversarial verification that catches what self-verification misses. Fresh-context verifiers attack proofs with specific failure patterns. Calibrated abstention over bluffing.",
  "longDescription": "Launches **8-12 parallel solver agents** (tuned by model tier), each running up to **5 internal solve-verify-correct rounds** with no computation tools allowed. After stripping reasoning traces, fresh-context adversarial verifiers attack proofs using pattern-specific checks: specialization to open problems, `2x2` counterexamples, and hypothesis condition verification. Asymmetric voting requires **4 HOLDS** to confirm but only **2 HOLE FOUND** to reject. Includes reference files for solver heuristics, adversarial prompts, known constructions, and verifier patterns. Produces clean LaTeX/PDF output after verification passes. Supports IMO, Putnam, USAMO, and AIME problems.",
  "compatibility": [
    "claude"
  ],
